<HL>
   Who's News:
   Modine Names Savage
   To Added Top Post
</HL>
<DATE>
09/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS MODI
</CO>
<IN>
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
</IN>
<LP>
   RACINE, Wis.-- Modine Manufacturing Co. said Richard T.
Savage, president and chief operating officer, will be named
to the additional post of chief executive officer at the end
of December.
   Mr. Savage, 52 years old, succeeds Earl E. Richter, who
will retire from the post.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Richter, 67, will continue as chairman of the board.
He joined Modine in 1948 and has held a variety of positions
with the maker of automotive parts and heating and air
conditioning equipment.
   Mr. Savage joined Modine in 1970 and has held his current
posts since February 1989.
</TEXT>
